# Enterprise Decision Ledger (EDL) — Governance Constitution

Status: **ENTERPRISE APPROVED** · P0 Go-Live Critical · Constitutional

This is **NOT** an Audit Log.  
This is **NOT** the Dialogue Center.

## Constitutional principles (frozen)

1. Facts are immutable.
2. Enterprise history must never be rewritten.
3. Business rules are versioned.
4. Commercial agreements are versioned.
5. Historical calculations remain historically correct.
6. Every important enterprise decision must leave a permanent, time-stamped, explainable record.

## Purpose

EDL is the constitutional memory of Catalyst One. Configuration and commercial changes are append-only ledger entries — never silent overwrites.

## When to record

Create an EDL entry for: Commission Structure · Partner/Lender Commercials · Product Rules · Credit Policies · Workflow/Stage/SLA Configuration · Document Checklist · Business Rules · Policy Engine · Credit & Risk Engine · Experience Console · Organization Settings · User Role / Permission changes · any future Enterprise Engine configuration.

Categories are configurable via `EDL_CHANGE_CATEGORIES`.

## Required fields

Ledger ID · Date/Time · Requested By · Approved By · Implemented By · Previous Value · New Value · Business Justification (mandatory) · Effective From · Effective Until · Version Number · Impact Scope · Change Type · Related Engine · Related Entity

## Temporal integrity

Future changes affect **future** transactions only unless an explicit migration runs. Historical transactions keep the rule / commercial version effective on their creation date.

## Chanakya

Chanakya uses EDL as a knowledge source (`resolveChanakyaEdlExplanation`). Chanakya explains history. Chanakya **never invents** history.

## Implementation SSOT (Phase 1)

- Types: `src/types/enterprise-decision-ledger.ts` (+ ports)
- Constants: `src/constants/enterprise-decision-ledger/`
- Engine: `src/lib/enterprise-decision-ledger/`
- UI: `/admin/enterprise-decision-ledger`
- Emitters (Phase 1): ECG config changes, Product Library drafts, Credit Risk policy audits, EPDE policy registration, commercial versioning APIs

Database structure = TypeScript domain + ports; Prisma adapters later via `configureEdlPorts()`.

## Do not

- Overwrite or delete ledger rows
- Silently mutate original lead source / campaign / creator / creation date
- Auto-recalculate historical commissions when a new commercial version publishes
- Treat EDL as Dialogue Center or a generic audit dump
